headline: Sempra and ConocoPhillips Extend Partnership with Offtake Agreement for Port Arthur LNG Phase 2
summary: Sempra (NYSE: SRE) today announced that its subsidiary, Sempra Infrastructure, and ConocoPhillips (NYSE: COP) have signed a definitive 20-year sale and purchase agreement (SPA) for 4 million tonnes per annum (Mtpa) of LNG offtake from the Port Arthur LNG Phase 2 development project in Jefferson County, Texas.

headline: ConocoPhillips further expands LNG business with additional Gulf Coast offtake agreement
summary: HOUSTON, August 21, 2025--ConocoPhillips has signed a long-term sales and purchase agreement to purchase 4 MTPA of LNG from the Port Arthur LNG Phase 2 project.

headline: How Investors May Respond To ConocoPhillips (COP) Higher Revenue and Output Amid Lower Oil Prices
summary: In August 2025, ConocoPhillips reported second quarter results showing increased revenues to US$14.74 billion and higher production, but lower net income and earnings per share compared to the previous year, while also declaring a quarterly dividend and confirming ongoing share buybacks. An interesting insight is that while production volumes rose, the company faced a significantly lower realized oil price, which weighed on profitability despite robust operational performance and continued...
